answer:
how do i erase an ask and idea from my brain

kidding. if i’m being real, i could totally see them doing this lmao. it would be a real “fuck you” to fans of villaneve, but it would be in line with the characters of the show so far. like it would be in character and make sense. it would just do the shippers super dirty.


i gotta believe they wouldn’t fuck us over like that, but who knows.

summary: just wanna say ty for expressing how emerald did have a disconnect from the characters despite the majority disliking any...
question: just wanna say ty for expressing how emerald did have a disconnect from the characters despite the majority disliking any negativity abt s2. ur brave 🙌🏼
answer:
thank you!! i try to remain objective, even though this is my favorite show on television. i can’t let how much i love a thing corrupt my honest to god criticism of it.

i go to school to just analyze stuff like this. i was in a class where we literally watched the pilot of killing eve and analyzed the shit out of it. if i was disillusioned or put my critiques aside in favor of blind support, i feel as if i’m sort of betraying my education. i want to have a credible opinion of media.


i love this show so fucking much, but this season didn’t compare to the first, and there are many reasons why. i can elaborate on them in the future, if anyone is curious. i probably need to do a rewatch of the second season as a whole, though.

summary: hi, I read your reply-post like 3 hrs ago abt suzanne and how she has more tv experience and seems to be more collaborative in a...
question: hi, I read your reply-post like 3 hrs ago abt suzanne and how she has more tv experience and seems to be more collaborative in a way emerald wasn't and her script doctoring  experience and i haven't stopped thinking about it because honestly like.. thank you. omg those post-finale interviews fucked me up and what you said on the actors kind of resenting the way emerald didn't rly ask for their input makes so much sense (but obvs no one is going to say it outright)!!
answer:
they legally can’t say it outright! since the start of press for season 2, i’ve sensed a difference in how jodie and sandra talk about the show and writers vs the press for season 1.

they just seemed… less enthusiastic. maybe disappointed? i know i was.


i have faith in suzanne. i trust her. i’m going to remain cautiously optimistic because i’d rather her than emerald (who clearly doesn’t understand some of the characters). she is a tv writer first and foremost. that should provide some relief.

summary: 6 Book Recommendations for Fans of Killing Eve [via Bookish] Are you addicted to the intriguing mystery and eccentric assassins...
caption:
6 Book Recommendations for Fans of Killing Eve

[via Bookish]

Are you addicted to the intriguing mystery and eccentric assassins of Killing Eve? We are! Glues to your TV every week, dying to know what Villanelle and Eve will do next in their game of cat and mouse? Here are 6 mystery novels that fans of Killing Eve will want to start reading ASAP:

  1. Save Me from Dangerous Men by S.A. Lelchuk
  2. My Lovely Wife by Samantha Downing
  3. My Sister, the Serial Killer by Oyinkan Braithwaite
  4. Baby Teeth by Zoje Stage
  5. The Perfect Girlfriend by Karen Hamilton
  6. Codename Villanelle by Luke Jennings
